        "# MSCI-Style Momentum Index Backtest\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook implements an MSCI-style Momentum Index backtest for the Indian equity market using Yahoo Finance data as the primary data source.\n",
        "\n",
        "The implementation includes:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Scheduled semi-annual reviews\n",
        "- Ad-hoc volatility-triggered reviews\n",
        "- 6M and 12M momentum scoring\n",
        "- Risk adjustment using 3Y weekly volatility\n",
        "- Corporate action handling based on available adjusted price data and reviewed event files\n",
        "- Fixed-number-of-securities selection logic\n",
        "- Issuer-level weight capping\n",
        "- Performance analytics and visualization\n",
        "- Cost analysis\n",
        "\n",
        "## Key Assumptions, Limitations, and Biases\n",
        "\n",
        "- Yahoo Finance adjusted close prices are used as the primary market data source.\n",
        "- NIFTY 500 constituents are used as a practical proxy for the Indian parent universe because official MSCI India constituent and weighting data are not freely available.\n",
        "- Historical float-adjusted market capitalization weights are unavailable; therefore, parent universe weights are approximated in certain sections of the implementation.\n",
        "- The backtest may contain survivorship bias because the current NIFTY 500 constituent universe is used instead of fully reconstructed historical index membership.\n",
        "- Historical constituent additions, deletions, mergers, acquisitions, suspensions, and ticker changes may not be completely captured.\n",
        "- Corporate action handling depends on Yahoo Finance adjusted price availability and may differ from official MSCI treatment.\n",
        "- Yahoo Finance data may contain occasional missing values, stale observations, or revision inconsistencies.\n",
        "- Transaction costs  and slippage are based on assumptions and may differ from real-world implementation costs.\n",
        "- Parent index weights used for market capitalization coverage calculations are approximated and may differ from official MSCI float-adjusted parent index weights.\n",
        "-Risk-free rates are approximated using static country-level assumptions  which is the 3-Month NSE MIBOR benchmark\n",
        "- The 3-Month NSE MIBOR rate is approximated using publicly available FBIL benchmark data and related market references obtained through online sources. Since continuous historical MIBOR time-series data was not readily available, a fixed representative rate assumption was used across the historical backtest period."
      ],
      "id": "X-ANa0U7iJy6"
